# UI Component Standards

## Core Rule

**Rule**: All UI components must follow TypeScript patterns, TailwindCSS conventions, and accessibility standards.

## Component Structure

**Rule**: Use typed props with default export and proper TypeScript interfaces.

**Example**:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import React from 'react';

interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
}

const variants = {
  primary: 'bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700',
  secondary: 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-300',
  ghost: 'bg-transparent hover:bg-gray-100',
};

const sizes = {
  sm: 'px-3 py-1.5 text-sm',
  md: 'px-4 py-2 text-base',
  lg: 'px-6 py-3 text-lg',
};

export default function Button({
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'md',
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500',
        variants[variant],
        sizes[size],
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## TailwindCSS Conventions

**Rule**: Use TailwindCSS utilities with `cn()` for conditional classes.

### Class Merging

**Use**: `cn()` utility from `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes.

**Example**:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// ✅ Good: Conditional classes with cn()
<div
  className={cn(
    'p-4 rounded-lg transition-colors',
    isActive && 'bg-blue-500 text-white',
    isDisabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'
  )}
/>

// ❌ Bad: Inline styles
<div style={{ padding: '16px', borderRadius: '8px' }} />
```

### Design Tokens

**Rule**: Use Tailwind design tokens (spacing, colors) instead of arbitrary values.

**Example**:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Using design tokens
<div className="p-4 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg" />

// ❌ Bad: Arbitrary values
<div className="p-[16px] bg-[#2563eb] text-[#ffffff] rounded-[8px]" />
```

### Dark Mode

**Rule**: Implement dark mode with `dark:` prefix.

**Example**:

```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
  Content
</div>
```

**Reference**: Configure `tailwind.config.js` with `darkMode: 'class'`.

## Accessibility Requirements

**Rule**: All interactive elements must be accessible.

### Keyboard Support

**Requirements**:
- ✅ All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- ✅ Focus indicators visible
- ✅ Tab order logical

**Example**:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Accessible button with keyboard support
<button
  aria-label="Close modal"
  onClick={onClose}
  onKeyDown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
      e.preventDefault();
      onClose();
    }
  }}
  className="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:outline-none"
>
  <XIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</button>

// ❌ Bad: Div as button (not keyboard accessible)
<div onClick={onClose}>
  <XIcon />
</div>
```

### Semantic HTML

**Rule**: Use semantic HTML elements.

**Examples**:
- `<button>` for buttons (not `<div>` with onClick)
- `<nav>` for navigation
- `<main>` for main content
- `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<section>` for structure

### ARIA Labels

**Rule**: Provide ARIA labels for icon-only buttons and non-text content.

**Example**:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Icon-only button with aria-label
<button aria-label="Delete item">
  <TrashIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</button>

// ✅ Good: Form input with label
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" />
```

### Focus Management

**Rule**: Ensure focus indicators are visible and logical.

**Example**:

```tsx
<button className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2">
  Click me
</button>
```

**Reference**: `code-quality/01_code-standards.mdc` for accessibility standards.

## shadcn/ui Integration

**Rule**: Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui` directory.

### Import Pattern

**Example**:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Import from components/ui
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTrigger } from '@/components/ui/dialog';

// Use as-is
<Button variant="default">Click me</Button>

// Or extend with composition
interface SaveButtonProps extends React.ComponentProps<typeof Button> {
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export function SaveButton({ isLoading, ...props }: SaveButtonProps) {
  return (
    <Button variant="default" disabled={isLoading} {...props}>
      {isLoading ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
    </Button>
  );
}
```

### Component Extension

**Rule**: Extend shadcn/ui components via composition, not modification.

**Example**:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Composition
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

export function PrimaryButton(props: React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>) {
  return <Button variant="default" {...props} />;
}

// ❌ Bad: Modifying source files
// Don't edit @/components/ui/button.tsx directly
```

## Component Props Pattern

**Rule**: Extend native HTML attributes for better TypeScript support.

**Example**:

```tsx
interface CardProps extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement> {
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
}

export function Card({ title, description, className, children, ...props }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('rounded-lg border p-6', className)} {...props}>
      {title && <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold">{title}</h3>}
      {description && <p className="text-sm text-gray-600">{description}</p>}
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## File Organization

**Rule**: Organize components in a clear structure.

**Structure**:
```
components/
├── ui/              # shadcn/ui components
│   ├── button.tsx
│   └── dialog.tsx
├── features/        # Feature-specific components
│   └── auth/
│       └── LoginForm.tsx
└── shared/          # Shared components
    └── Header.tsx
```

**Naming**: Use PascalCase for component files: `Button.tsx`, `UserCard.tsx`.
